Jan 16
Release Notes
This strategy is an intraday trading system designed for very short timeframes (2–5 minutes).
It combines Fibonacci volatility bands, RSI momentum signals, and strict risk control to capture short-term price reversals within active market phases.

🔧 Core Components

1. Fibonacci Volatility Bands

Based on a VWMA (Volume Weighted Moving Average).

Upper and lower bands are calculated using standard deviation multipliers.

These bands define:

Overextended price zones

Dynamic take-profit targets

Mean-reversion areas

2. RSI Confirmation

RSI is used to detect oversold and overbought conditions.

Trades are only triggered when RSI crosses back from extreme levels, confirming momentum reversal.

📈 Trade Logic
Long Entry

Price reaches the lower Fibonacci band

RSI crosses upward from oversold

Market conditions allow sufficient distance to the target

Short Entry

Price reaches the upper Fibonacci band

RSI crosses downward from overbought

Market conditions allow sufficient distance to the target
